                        <container
                            cq:panelTitle="What is a Savings Account?"
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="icici/components/container">
                            <text
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="icici/components/text"
                                text="&lt;p>A Savings Account is a fundamental financial product offered by ICICI Bank, designed to help individuals save and grow their money. With ICICI Bank Savings Account, customers can experience the convenience of easy access to their funds,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.icicibank.com/personal-banking/accounts/savings-account/interest-rates&quot;>competitive interest rates&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;and a range of Digital Banking services. Start your journey towards saving money with ICICI Bank Savings Account today.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
                        </container>
                        <item_1746009261790
                            cq:panelTitle="What are the interest rates for ICICI Bank Savings Account?"
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="icici/components/container">
                            <text
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="icici/components/text"
                                text="&lt;p>ICICI Bank ensures competitive returns on your deposited funds. With a focus on financial growth and increased savings, we offer attractive interest rates from 2.75% to 3.25%. By opening a Savings Account with ICICI Bank, you can enjoy the benefits of reliable and secure banking.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
                        </item_1746009261790>
                        <item_1746009265257
                            cq:panelTitle="What is the minimum balance required to be maintained in ICICI Bank Savings Account?"
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="icici/components/container">
                            <text
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="icici/components/text"
                                text="&lt;p>ICICI Bank Savings Account provides an easy way to save money and offers a fixed rate of interest.&amp;nbsp;The minimum balance required to be maintained in an ICICI Bank Savings Account varies as per the Account variant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
                        </item_1746009265257>
                        <item_1746009270573
                            cq:panelTitle="How is the Minimum Monthly Average Balance (MAB) calculated?"
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="icici/components/container">
                            <text
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="icici/components/text"
                                text="&lt;p>The Monthly Average Balance (MAB) is calculated on a simple average of EOD balances for a calendar month. The MAB is calculated by adding the closing ledger balance of the account of each day from the start of the month to the end of the month. Then the total sum is divided by the number of days in that month.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
                        </item_1746009270573>
                        <item_1746009275456
                            cq:panelTitle="Can I get a chequebook after opening a Savings Account?"
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="icici/components/container">
                            <text
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="icici/components/text"
                                text="&lt;p>Your chequebook will be issued only upon request after you have successfully completed your KYC verification. You can request for a chequebook by logging in to ICICI Bank Internet Banking or the iMobile App.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>iMobile App:&amp;nbsp;Go to Services &amp;gt; Chequebook Services &amp;gt; Issue Chequebook&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Internet Banking:&amp;nbsp;Go to Bank Accounts &amp;gt; Accounts &amp;gt; Chequebook request&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
                        </item_1746009275456>
